commit.message:
(PA-4725) Updates for ruby 3.2 support

This commit changes the dependencies for ruby 3.2 support. Also
in this update are github workflows to release to rubygems, as
well as testing on PR and push.
(maint) Updated fast gettext version req to 1.1 (minor digit)

(maint) Revert error for some versions of ruby

A simple rubocop fix caused an error in older versions of ruby. This fix
uses the original `send` command instead.
(maint) add release procedure to readme

(maint) contrain gettext version to < 3.3.0

gettext 3.3.0 has dropped support for < ruby v2.5. This commit
constrains the version of gettext to < than that y version.
rubocop: autofix

Don't depend on a legacy bundler release

It's currently impossible to install dependencies with `bundle
install..` on a modern distribution. bundler 2 is available since more
than a year.
(maint) Fix Rubocop
(maint) Fix spec test where environment variable has a value
(maint) Add CODEOWNERS
(maint) Fix rubocop

Add `date` require to metadata_pot.rb

Fixes the following error for Ruby 2.6:
```
uninitialized constant GettextSetup::MetadataPot::DateTime
```

(maint) Use new pot if msgcmp unavailable

If msgcmp isn't on the system, we were previously relying on the system
throwing an IOError that we could catch. Unfortunately, this wasn't
consistently happening. This commit adds an additional check to
explicitly print out a warning if msgcmp is not available and to
proceed with replacing the old pot with the new one.
(maint) Appease Rubocop

Fixes: https://github.com/puppetlabs/gettext-setup-gem/issues/64

(maint) Updates for rubocop

(GH-61) Handle initial nil value

Previously, if GettextSetup.initialize was called with a config.yaml, but
there were no corresponding language subdirectories, e.g. locales/ja,
then GettextSetup would set FastGettext.default_locale to nil.

The issue was because GettextSetup set FastGettext.default_available_locales
to an empty array in commit bc57b9af. However, FastGettext interpreted that
to mean there were no available locales! So later attempts to set the
FastGettext.default_locale were "filtered out", since the argument was
never one of the available locales.

One subtle issue here was that FastGettext.default_available_locales
defaults to nil. So Array union (`|`), could produce surprising results
the first time the Gettext.initialize method was called:

     $ ruby -e "puts nil | []"
     true

This commit removes the call to `FastGettext.default_available_locales = []`,
protects against calling Array union with nil, and sets the
default_available_locales before setting the default_locale, since the
latter depends on the former. This solves the original issue because
GettextSetup defaults to 'en' even if there are no local subdirectories.
So then that becomes an available locale, and our later attempt to set
the default locale is not filtered out.

This commit also preserves the behavior of INTL-18, which joins locales
across multiple projects, instead of letting the last one overwrite.

(maint) Clear FastGettext global state between tests

Clear FastGettext global state after each test to avoid order dependent spec
failures.
(maint) Fix README.md

(maint) Remove Rubocop TargetRubyVersion check

When running this check, Rubocop appears to assume the version running
the test is the minimum ruby version, which is in conflict with what is
defined in the gemspec. TargetRubyVersion can't be less than 2.0, so
this removes that check.

(INTL-31) Refactor rake tasks to not setup FastGettext runtime

Prior to this commit the Gettext:Pot module would setup the FastGettext
config and runtime. This would cause strange conflicts with other calls
to FastGettext (for example, when calling the rake task in an
environment that also contains Puppet 5.3.3) so we decided that
since the rake tasks do not require the FastGettext runtime config,
they should not try to set it up.
This commit refactors the GettextSetup.initialize method to call out
to a GettextSetup.initialize_config method, that only configures the
file-related info for the library. Then the GettextSetup:Pot module
is updated to call the GettextSetup.initialized_config method instead
of initialize. As far as I know, the GettextSetup:Pot module is only
called by the rake tasks so hopefully this is a safe fix.

(FM-6415) create header_only option for pot generation

For the sake of consistency across POT files (ruby, puppet, metadata), it seems to make sense for the headers to all be created in one place. This change allows for the creation of 'blank' POT files, or POT files with only a header, by passing in a blank input file. This provides the following benefits:
- When POT files are merged, differences in header content can cause a lot of clutter in the final POT file. identical headers will cut down on this clutter substantially.
- The generate function can be used to create blank POT files to allow for the appending of POT files for other languages in the future
- Consistency is great
- GettextSetup knows a lot about the current project so it can provide header info that other libraries may not be able to, like project name, etc.

(FM-6323) - Copying Ruby POT rather than moving it

When the Ruby POT file is moved, it doesn't exist in the repo when
merging POT files. Copying means that it exists in the new location and
also the Ruby strings are contained in the merged file.
(maint) Deleting transient fixtures

(maint) Convert named parameters to hash

In order to be functional on JRuby 1.7.x, we cannot rely on features that are
only present in later releases of Ruby, like named parameters. This reverts some
code that used that new feature.

(PUP-7881) Put default locales at the front of available_locales

FastGettext prefers the first item in its list of available locales when
choosing a locale before it has been set by the user. However, we were
putting our defaults at the end of the list we use to initialize
FastGettext, meaning FastGettext was choosing an essentially random
locale as its initial value for `locale`. This commit updates the way we
 construct our `available_locales` list to put the defaults first.

Rake task to merge .pot files

Due to the nature of translating several different languages and files
during the translation of a module we need to be able to merge
.pot files - This task does so.

Allow pot task to take a filename
